We held each child back 1 year in school from their American age=20
peers, but did NOT change their actual birthdates.

Initially, I felt strongly that we should change their birthdates by=20
1 year -- but Jackson felt VERY strongly that we should not.  His=20
logic was that after we opted to change their Russian and Kazak=20
names -- the only "thing" they brought with them from Kaz was their=20
birthdates.

The school district initially placed a GREAT deal of pressure on us=20
to place them with their age peers, but we resisted and basically=20
demanded that they be placed back 1 year -- which was within our=20
rights to do -- although the school district tried to convince us=20
otherwise.  They kept telling us that ESL would catch the kids up=20
soon enough -- but given the fact that neither child had much formal=20
education, we didn't feel starting them in 2nd and 4th grade was in=20
their best interest.

So, although our kids were 8 and 10 years old when they came home in=20
April of 2000, we started them off in 1st and 3rd grade.  The kids=20
then attended 1st and 3rd grade summer school -- and we moved them on=20
to 2nd and 4th grade in September 2000, just over 4 months after they=20
came home. =20

Academically and socially, they were really still about a year behind=20
their classmates, maybe more, when they started 2nd and 4th grade=20
last year -- but by the end of the school year they were almost=20
working at grade level and were nearly on par socially with their=20
classmates.

In terms of their sizes, which was a MAJOR driver behind holding them=20
back 1 year -- I would say they were about in the middle of their=20
classes in terms of their heights and weights when they started=20
school.  HOWEVER, after being home for 16 months -- BOTH kids were at=20
the 60th percentile for height for their AGES -- making them two of=20
the tallest kids in their grades.

I don't have the exact figures on how much they grew -- but we know=20
that in the first 18 months after Nicholas left the orphanage he grew=20
more than 7 inches and Kira grew more than 6 inches and gained 11=20
pounds the first year home.

We did initially consider holding them back 2 years from their age=20
peers when they came home -- but we are VERY, VERY glad now that we=20
didn't do that.  If we had held them back 2 grades instead of just=20
one BOTH kids would have TOWERED over the other kids right now. =20
Academically they would have been better off, but socially it would=20
have been disasterous.  As it is now, the kids look noticeably bigger=20
than many of their classmates -- which is incredible given how small=20
they were compared to most of the other kids when they came home.

Anyway, this is what we did....

Laura



