this summer.<<

Not necessarily.  Many of these kids have no idea how old they are --=20
and some "think" they are one age but are actually another (usually=20
older) age.  It depends on what the practice is in the orphanage --=20
some recognize birthdays and group kids by age -- while others do=20
little, if anything, to recognize birthdays or segregate the kids=20
according to age groups.  Our kids knew how old they were, and the=20
season their birthday was in...but I suspect that was ONLY because=20
they were each in foster care and celebrated a birthday with their=20
foster families just before their adoptions.



